Between the "Security" days in Osceola and the all-important-after-the-election packed weekends of ballots dropping, we welcome a fresh Tuesday and the opportunity to unlock the news beyond big-screen romances ("Which way would I go if I were cropped out of this photo?") and sports scores ("Which Magic player acts most like a frat boy off the court?"). We also welcome this week’s fresh picks of news events/clubs/events/press releases that we are calling out for your reading/viewing/buying/listening pleasure.

Next week, we roll out an all-new GEL message board discussion tool on this website.

Bulgaria's Parliament on 21 February rejected a motion to declassify information on the finances of the Bulgarian Black Sea Fleet in the period stretching from 2001 to 2008, thus throwing a legal spanner in the works of an audit into what has been unspecified is at "Arms Ombudsman's request."
